# =============================================================================
# Model: glm-4.7-flash:opencode_slow_max_ctx_thinking
# Base:  glm-4.7-flash-max-ctx:latest (29.9B MoE-lite, Q4_K_M)
# GPU:   Tesla P40, 23040 MiB VRAM
# Built: 2026-05-02
#
# PURPOSE
# -------
# Maximum context variant. Use for whole-repo analysis, very long opencode
# sessions, or large diffs where context depth matters more than latency.
# At ~10 tok/s the user is already waiting; thinking is left enabled to
# maximise quality on complex large-context tasks.
#
# For fast tool-use loops use glm-4.7-flash:opencode_no_think (~35 tok/s,
# 43520 token context).
#
# CHANGES FROM glm-4.7-flash-max-ctx:latest
# ------------------------------------------
# 1. num_ctx 202752
#    Full native context length of the model. The KV cache spills heavily to
#    CPU RAM above 43520 tokens, but generation remains usable (~10 tok/s) all
#    the way to the native limit. See benchmark.
#
# 2. temperature 1 — kept unchanged (see note in no_think variant)
#
# 3. SYSTEM — explicit empty-content instruction (same as no_think variant)
#
# BENCHMARK — Tesla P40, 2026-05-02
# ----------------------------------
# High-context sweep (num_predict=200):
#
#   num_ctx   gen tok/s   notes
#   -------   ---------   -----
#    43520       35.71    fully in VRAM (fast variant)
#    44032       26.33    partial CPU offload begins
#    57344       17.40    partial offload
#    73728       15.68    partial offload
#    81920       14.46    partial offload
#    98304       13.95    partial offload
#   114688       13.13    partial offload
#   131072       11.83    partial offload
#   163840       10.20    partial offload
#   196608       10.24    partial offload
#   202752        9.98    native context limit — still usable  ← chosen
#
# Speed declines gradually from the cliff at 44032 to ~10 tok/s at the native
# limit. No hard failure observed at any tested size.
#
# TOOL-CALL TESTS (all passed, same as no_think variant)
# =============================================================================

FROM glm-4.7-flash-max-ctx:latest

# 202752 = full native context. KV cache spills to CPU RAM; ~10 tok/s on P40.
PARAMETER num_ctx 202752

PARAMETER temperature 1

SYSTEM """You are an expert software engineer assistant. Follow all tool-use instructions exactly as specified. Use the tools provided to read, write, and execute code. Respond concisely with working solutions.
IMPORTANT: When making tool calls, the message content MUST be empty. Do not narrate, explain, or announce what you are about to do — output only the tool call."""
